casebody.data:
Luis A. VILLEGAS-ROSA, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 81088 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: November 20, 2018 Susan L. Hogan, Kansas City, MO, for appellant. Robert J. Bartholomew, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent. Before Division Three: Gary D. Witt, Presiding Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge ORDER Per curiam:

Appellant Luis Villegas-Rosa ("Villegas-Rosa") is appealing the denial of his Amended Rule 24.035 motion following an evidentiary hearing. Villegas-Rosa sought to vacate his guilty plea and sentence to a class A felony of second degree murder pursuant to section 565.021. For reasons explained more fully in a memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
